article_title: Oil Prices Slightly Up; U.S. Crude Inventory Data in Focus
article_text:
Crude oil prices regained ground in early Asia trade Wednesday but moves were largely subdued as the market looked toward the weekly U.S. crude inventory and production data due later.

On the New York Mercantile Exchange, light, sweet crude futures for delivery in February traded at $36.02 a barrel at 0324 GMT, up $0.05 in the Globex electronic session. February Brent crude on London’s ICE Futures exchange rose $0.02 to $36.44 a...
